<plot>John Nizzari gives an intriguing inside perspective of a union construction site and humanizes the nameless men who build New York City. Through a series of interviews and debates, the outspoken workers candidly express their views on religion, government and race. Soon, camaraderie and banter give way to rage and suffering. Captured with raw insight, tensions ultimately build and graphic events unfold, during the rise of a luxury condominium on the west side of Manhattan.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?277852</url></doc>
